1
00:01:47,719 --> 00:01:48,040
[Miao Jing,]

2
00:01:48,599 --> 00:01:49,060
[Hongshen...]

3
00:01:49,060 --> 00:01:50,340
Miao Jing's got a family emergency these days.

4
00:01:51,299 --> 00:01:52,340
Could she take two days off?

5
00:01:53,319 --> 00:01:53,700
[Okay.]

6
00:01:54,439 --> 00:01:55,159
[May I ask]

7
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:56,000
[how is she?]

8
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:56,500
Sorry.

9
00:01:59,739 --> 00:02:00,140
Thanks for your help.

10
00:02:29,419 --> 00:02:30,800
No empty hearses or refrigerated caskets available?

11
00:02:33,199 --> 00:02:33,719
Alright then,

12
00:02:34,139 --> 00:02:35,319
I'll arrange a car myself.

13
00:02:35,439 --> 00:02:36,199
I'll send the body today.

14
00:02:55,060 --> 00:02:55,560
Hello, Zhou.

15
00:03:20,539 --> 00:03:21,460
My condolences to you all.

16
00:03:24,199 --> 00:03:24,960
Appreciate it, Zhou.

17
00:03:25,659 --> 00:03:26,500
Where'd you get the car?

18
00:03:26,919 --> 00:03:28,120
The funeral parlor owner.

19
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:29,639
I've borrowed their hearse

20
00:03:29,780 --> 00:03:31,080
with a refrigerated casket before.

21
00:03:34,120 --> 00:03:35,000
After a busy night,

22
00:03:35,879 --> 00:03:36,379
you must be famished.

23
00:03:36,939 --> 00:03:37,219
Here you are.

24
00:03:38,259 --> 00:03:38,659
Have some.

25
00:03:44,180 --> 00:03:45,460
Eat even if you have no appetite.

26
00:03:46,199 --> 00:03:47,620
We've got lots of physical work ahead.

27
00:03:48,139 --> 00:03:49,560
Don't wear yourself out.

28
00:03:50,840 --> 00:03:51,479
Don't worry.

29
00:03:52,020 --> 00:03:52,900
We're all here to help.

30
00:03:54,699 --> 00:03:55,659
Thanks, Zhou.

31
00:03:56,379 --> 00:03:58,020
We'll take her to the morgue first.

32
00:03:58,319 --> 00:03:58,800
Okay.

33
00:03:59,479 --> 00:04:00,039
Han,

34
00:04:00,219 --> 00:04:00,819
take them there.

35
00:04:00,900 --> 00:04:01,439
- Okay.
- This way please.

36
00:04:15,340 --> 00:04:16,720
Family, please identify the body.

37
00:04:16,920 --> 00:04:18,019
Then sign the handover papers

38
00:04:18,019 --> 00:04:19,720
and the death certificate.

39
00:04:33,459 --> 00:04:34,079
I'll do it.

40
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:39,259
I'm fine with that.

41
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:08,920
Finished?

42
00:06:20,879 --> 00:06:22,079
Come sign here then.

43
00:06:40,399 --> 00:06:41,639
I also need your fingerprint.

44
00:06:54,040 --> 00:06:54,519
Miao Jing.

45
00:07:20,839 --> 00:07:22,259
I just felt a sense of oppression.

46
00:07:23,300 --> 00:07:23,800
Let's go.

47
00:07:47,740 --> 00:07:50,279
The farewell ceremony will begin.

48
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:52,439
All relatives and guests,

49
00:07:52,439 --> 00:07:53,959
please step forward and take your positions.

50
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:57,500
All relatives and guests,

51
00:07:57,500 --> 00:07:59,000
please step forward and take your positions.

52
00:08:02,720 --> 00:08:04,939
Immediate family members, stand in the first row.

53
00:08:06,980 --> 00:08:08,980
Immediate family members, stand in the first row.

54
00:08:14,759 --> 00:08:15,420
Today,

55
00:08:15,980 --> 00:08:16,500
we,

56
00:08:16,500 --> 00:08:19,000
with heavy hearts,

57
00:08:19,759 --> 00:08:20,680
gather here

58
00:08:20,680 --> 00:08:22,360
to hold this farewell ceremony.

59
00:08:22,759 --> 00:08:23,939
We mourn deeply

60
00:08:24,019 --> 00:08:25,500
for Ms. Wei Mingzhen.

61
00:08:26,360 --> 00:08:28,660
We bid a heartfelt farewell to Ms. Wei

62
00:08:28,660 --> 00:08:30,060
on her final journey.

63
00:08:39,460 --> 00:08:40,360
Silence.

64
00:08:40,740 --> 00:08:41,639
Mourn.

65
00:08:47,179 --> 00:08:48,340
End of silent tribute.

66
00:08:52,220 --> 00:08:52,759
Now,

67
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:54,360
let us bow

68
00:08:54,779 --> 00:08:55,860
three times

69
00:08:55,899 --> 00:08:57,980
to Ms. Wei,

70
00:08:58,539 --> 00:08:59,600
to express

71
00:09:00,159 --> 00:09:01,240
our grief.

72
00:09:05,779 --> 00:09:08,820
Everyone, one bow.

73
00:09:12,519 --> 00:09:13,399
Wei Mingzhen is dead.

74
00:09:17,320 --> 00:09:18,059
Who are you?

75
00:09:24,159 --> 00:09:25,240
You're Wei Mingzhen's daughter, right?

76
00:09:25,899 --> 00:09:27,139
Your mom owes us over 200,000 yuan.

77
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:28,100
But look at her.

78
00:09:28,360 --> 00:09:28,940
She just kicked the bucket

79
00:09:29,279 --> 00:09:29,860
without money left.

80
00:09:32,379 --> 00:09:33,179
No matter the reason,

81
00:09:34,019 --> 00:09:34,799
causing a scene at a funeral

82
00:09:34,879 --> 00:09:35,700
is inappropriate, isn't it?

83
00:09:37,700 --> 00:09:38,679
The decency

84
00:09:38,960 --> 00:09:39,799
won't pay off her debts.

85
00:09:40,460 --> 00:09:41,360
If I don't come here now,

86
00:09:41,700 --> 00:09:42,159
I'm afraid that

87
00:09:42,159 --> 00:09:42,899
I'll never get my money back.

88
00:09:43,620 --> 00:09:44,960
I know exactly tricks like yours.

89
00:09:45,500 --> 00:09:46,019
You love pushing the line that

90
00:09:46,159 --> 00:09:47,259
debts die with the debtor.

91
00:09:47,659 --> 00:09:48,440
No way.

92
00:09:49,340 --> 00:09:50,159
Talk this over outside.

93
00:09:53,480 --> 00:09:54,279
You wanna run away?

94
00:09:54,860 --> 00:09:55,299
Let go.

95
00:09:55,639 --> 00:09:56,700
Don't push your luck.

96
00:10:06,440 --> 00:10:07,379
How much does she owe you?

97
00:10:08,299 --> 00:10:09,080
230,000.

98
00:10:09,539 --> 00:10:10,700
She signed the IOU last July.

99
00:10:11,039 --> 00:10:12,480
It's two months overdue.

100
00:10:13,139 --> 00:10:14,220
How did you find this place?

101
00:10:15,559 --> 00:10:16,559
Her number's disconnected.

102
00:10:16,980 --> 00:10:17,720
The contract on file

103
00:10:17,720 --> 00:10:19,179
lists her daughter's contact info,

104
00:10:19,519 --> 00:10:20,179
namely you.

105
00:10:20,639 --> 00:10:21,379
Who knows if you heard the news

106
00:10:21,379 --> 00:10:22,440
and planned to skip town?

107
00:10:24,279 --> 00:10:24,820
Listen.

108
00:10:25,279 --> 00:10:26,059
We actually

109
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:26,740
lent out every cent,

110
00:10:26,740 --> 00:10:28,080
no tricks involved.

111
00:10:28,659 --> 00:10:30,080
We wouldn't show up at such a sensitive time

112
00:10:30,620 --> 00:10:31,899
if we could track her down

113
00:10:32,179 --> 00:10:32,799
anywhere else.

114
00:10:33,460 --> 00:10:34,019
Where's the contract?

115
00:10:42,159 --> 00:10:42,620
It's fine.

116
00:10:42,840 --> 00:10:43,299
It's just a copy.

117
00:10:43,399 --> 00:10:43,759
Hand it to him.

118
00:10:59,360 --> 00:11:00,100
Pay double for every yuan borrowed.

119
00:11:01,460 --> 00:11:02,019
Predatory usury?

120
00:11:05,259 --> 00:11:06,360
It is illegal.

121
00:11:06,799 --> 00:11:07,220
Besides,

122
00:11:07,580 --> 00:11:08,399
she has passed away now.

123
00:11:08,860 --> 00:11:10,240
Her debts are none of my business.

124
00:11:12,320 --> 00:11:13,919
You can't just say it's illegal like that!

125
00:11:18,360 --> 00:11:19,480
You harass people at their homes,

126
00:11:20,059 --> 00:11:20,980
disturb neighbors,

127
00:11:21,500 --> 00:11:22,220
and issue personal threats.

128
00:11:23,779 --> 00:11:24,580
I know every dirty trick

129
00:11:25,259 --> 00:11:25,899
you pull.

130
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:31,840
I don't have time to argue with you now.

131
00:11:32,700 --> 00:11:33,220
If you know what's good for you,

132
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:34,659
get out of here at once.

133
00:11:37,440 --> 00:11:38,480
Who do you think

134
00:11:38,580 --> 00:11:39,419
you're talking to?

135
00:11:40,059 --> 00:11:40,679
Sir!

136
00:11:40,860 --> 00:11:41,740
- It hurts!
- Sir!

137
00:11:41,840 --> 00:11:42,419
Let him go!

138
00:11:43,720 --> 00:11:44,299
It really hurts!

139
00:11:44,360 --> 00:11:45,419
If you keep harassing us,

140
00:11:45,940 --> 00:11:46,799
we'll call the police to handle this.

141
00:11:47,720 --> 00:11:48,700
Call the cops now!

142
00:11:49,039 --> 00:11:50,080
I don't care!

143
00:11:50,159 --> 00:11:50,779
I've got the IOU and contract!

144
00:11:50,840 --> 00:11:51,220
It hurts!

145
00:11:51,220 --> 00:11:51,600
Sir!

146
00:11:51,960 --> 00:11:52,980
I'm the police!

147
00:11:54,840 --> 00:11:55,279
Let go of him.

148
00:11:55,440 --> 00:11:55,980
What happened?

149
00:12:05,139 --> 00:12:05,820
Here are the IOU and contract.

150
00:12:15,720 --> 00:12:16,860
This is usury

151
00:12:17,740 --> 00:12:18,620
and it has no legal standing.

152
00:12:19,620 --> 00:12:21,360
A debt should be repaid, which is common sense.

153
00:12:21,639 --> 00:12:22,059
Sir,

154
00:12:22,360 --> 00:12:23,659
we're not running a charity here.

155
00:12:24,059 --> 00:12:24,919
Wei Mingzhen is dead.

156
00:12:25,799 --> 00:12:26,639
But as her child,

157
00:12:26,840 --> 00:12:27,740
she still holds the obligation to settle the debt, right?

158
00:12:31,039 --> 00:12:32,200
She only needs to pay back the principal.

159
00:12:32,759 --> 00:12:34,240
The double repayment clause in this contract

160
00:12:34,779 --> 00:12:35,259
is invalid.

161
00:12:36,019 --> 00:12:37,360
Even if your usury business

162
00:12:37,500 --> 00:12:38,799
only violates civil law,

163
00:12:38,919 --> 00:12:40,159
I can't detain you right now.

164
00:12:40,559 --> 00:12:41,120
However,

165
00:12:41,120 --> 00:12:42,759
during debt collection,

166
00:12:43,059 --> 00:12:44,480
if you harm

167
00:12:44,480 --> 00:12:45,820
anyone's personal safety or property,

168
00:12:47,059 --> 00:12:48,100
public security authorities have the right

169
00:12:48,679 --> 00:12:49,379
to penalize you

170
00:12:49,460 --> 00:12:50,620
in accordance with the law.

171
00:12:51,919 --> 00:12:52,279
So,

172
00:12:53,120 --> 00:12:54,240
do you wanna come to the police station with me?

173
00:12:55,840 --> 00:12:56,360
Zhou.

174
00:12:59,440 --> 00:13:00,240
You guys head back first.

175
00:13:00,759 --> 00:13:01,759
You have my contact information.

176
00:13:01,759 --> 00:13:02,419
I won't run away.

177
00:13:02,700 --> 00:13:03,740
We can work out a repayment plan later

178
00:13:03,740 --> 00:13:04,679
to resolve this problem.

179
00:13:04,980 --> 00:13:06,399
But if you come back to cause trouble again,

180
00:13:06,960 --> 00:13:07,860
I won't show any mercy.

181
00:13:10,419 --> 00:13:10,960
Aren't you leaving yet?

182
00:13:13,779 --> 00:13:14,200
See ya.

183
00:13:18,840 --> 00:13:19,100
Let's go.

184
00:13:21,700 --> 00:13:22,620
Why don't you beat him up?

185
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:27,700
It's okay now.

186
00:13:29,899 --> 00:13:31,559
You need an elder to oversee the cremation inside.

187
00:13:32,320 --> 00:13:32,960
I'll head in first.

188
00:13:44,019 --> 00:13:45,779
It wasn't real until I saw her portrait just now.

189
00:13:47,360 --> 00:13:48,960
Only then did I truly realize she was gone.

190
00:14:05,159 --> 00:14:05,580
Miao Jing.

191
00:14:07,840 --> 00:14:08,700
Don't push yourself too hard.

192
00:14:13,179 --> 00:14:14,159
These past two days,

193
00:14:15,840 --> 00:14:17,519
I keep thinking about old times.

194
00:14:18,679 --> 00:14:19,639
I recall her

195
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:22,860
coming to take me away from my aunt's house,

196
00:14:23,960 --> 00:14:24,659
freeing me

197
00:14:24,659 --> 00:14:26,080
from living as a dependent relative.

198
00:14:27,779 --> 00:14:29,100
She brought me to Vineton

199
00:14:29,440 --> 00:14:30,279
where I met you,

200
00:14:31,100 --> 00:14:32,200
and finally had a real home.

201
00:14:34,419 --> 00:14:35,919
She bought dresses,

202
00:14:36,500 --> 00:14:37,519
boiled eggs,

203
00:14:38,220 --> 00:14:39,059
and gold jewelry for me.

204
00:14:41,980 --> 00:14:43,200
All I can remember

205
00:14:43,200 --> 00:14:44,620
are her kindnesses.

206
00:14:46,019 --> 00:14:47,279
I've somehow forgotten

207
00:14:49,100 --> 00:14:50,419
all her faults.

208
00:14:54,500 --> 00:14:55,340
Do you think she came back

209
00:14:55,340 --> 00:14:56,960
because she truly missed me,

210
00:14:58,240 --> 00:14:58,799
or only to

211
00:14:58,799 --> 00:15:00,179
dump all these troubles on me?

212
00:15:13,279 --> 00:15:13,700
Miao Jing.

213
00:15:15,639 --> 00:15:16,559
We're all ordinary people.

214
00:15:19,419 --> 00:15:20,320
It's only natural

215
00:15:20,399 --> 00:15:21,720
to grieve over something like this.

216
00:15:23,039 --> 00:15:23,940
It doesn't mean anything deeper.

217
00:15:25,419 --> 00:15:26,179
All the past,

218
00:15:28,080 --> 00:15:29,159
good or bad,

219
00:15:29,539 --> 00:15:30,299
is long gone.

220
00:15:33,639 --> 00:15:34,500
Joy

221
00:15:36,600 --> 00:15:37,320
or sorrow,

222
00:15:38,399 --> 00:15:39,539
don't force yourself to make decisions.

223
00:15:52,080 --> 00:15:53,100
Family members may place burial items

224
00:15:53,100 --> 00:15:54,379
inside this box.

225
00:15:54,879 --> 00:15:56,139
They will be returned

226
00:15:56,179 --> 00:15:57,279
with the ashes urn after cremation.

227
00:17:47,279 --> 00:17:49,119
I never had the luck to turn my fate around.

228
00:17:50,119 --> 00:17:50,799
But my brother,

229
00:17:51,819 --> 00:17:53,119
I have the means

230
00:17:55,279 --> 00:17:55,920
to show you

231
00:17:55,920 --> 00:17:57,500
what life with endless money

232
00:17:57,500 --> 00:17:58,799
really looks like.

233
00:18:06,980 --> 00:18:07,559
Here's to you.

234
00:18:08,720 --> 00:18:09,279
Brother,

235
00:18:10,180 --> 00:18:11,420
there's another favor I need to ask of you.

236
00:18:13,579 --> 00:18:14,619
You've got to help me

237
00:18:14,619 --> 00:18:15,319
go through this challenge.

238
00:18:16,160 --> 00:18:17,460
Make sure everything goes smoothly,

239
00:18:17,460 --> 00:18:18,359
without a single hitch.

240
00:18:26,059 --> 00:18:26,660
Mr. Zhang.

241
00:18:31,160 --> 00:18:32,400
Mr. Liu said that

242
00:18:32,920 --> 00:18:34,319
once we weather this crackdown,

243
00:18:34,519 --> 00:18:35,019
we can officially move shipments

244
00:18:35,019 --> 00:18:36,200
early next month.

245
00:18:36,599 --> 00:18:37,299
But....

246
00:18:38,119 --> 00:18:38,740
But what?

247
00:18:39,700 --> 00:18:41,339
The police have been watching us closely.

248
00:18:41,779 --> 00:18:42,640
What happened in Gangcheng

249
00:18:42,640 --> 00:18:43,660
came totally out of the blue.

250
00:18:44,059 --> 00:18:44,920
Do you think

251
00:18:45,519 --> 00:18:46,559
the police

252
00:18:46,559 --> 00:18:47,420
might know something?

253
00:18:50,079 --> 00:18:50,660
Sorry, Mr. Zhang.

254
00:18:50,880 --> 00:18:51,640
I spoke out of turn.

255
00:18:54,799 --> 00:18:55,339
It's been six years.

256
00:18:57,640 --> 00:18:58,920
Zhou Kang'an has been

257
00:18:59,160 --> 00:19:00,960
keeping his eyes

258
00:19:01,160 --> 00:19:01,819
on us,

259
00:19:02,740 --> 00:19:03,299
right?

260
00:19:04,460 --> 00:19:05,220
I've got used to it.

261
00:19:08,279 --> 00:19:08,700
Brother,

262
00:19:10,640 --> 00:19:11,660
I'll take the fall for you

263
00:19:12,119 --> 00:19:12,960
this time.

264
00:19:14,799 --> 00:19:15,480
Now we're even.

265
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:31,099
In the past,

266
00:19:31,380 --> 00:19:31,759
I always

267
00:19:31,759 --> 00:19:33,460
ate inside a tent.

268
00:19:34,059 --> 00:19:35,339
How could I eat by the side of the road?

269
00:19:41,500 --> 00:19:42,619
If Mr. Zhai were still here,

270
00:19:44,099 --> 00:19:45,339
none of these guys dare mess with us.

271
00:19:48,440 --> 00:19:49,279
Eat up.

272
00:19:49,880 --> 00:19:50,700
It's covered in dust.

273
00:19:51,559 --> 00:19:52,000
I'm not eating.

274
00:20:19,960 --> 00:20:21,680
I'll find a storage place tomorrow.

275
00:20:22,299 --> 00:20:23,680
and leave the ashes there for now.

276
00:20:24,119 --> 00:20:24,920
On the weekend,

277
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:26,960
I'll check out the local cemetery.

278
00:20:28,319 --> 00:20:29,160
No need to do that.

279
00:20:30,599 --> 00:20:31,319
Just keep the ashes

280
00:20:32,240 --> 00:20:33,099
here for the time being.

281
00:20:39,180 --> 00:20:40,140
What's your plan?

282
00:20:43,319 --> 00:20:44,059
What else can I do?

283
00:20:45,099 --> 00:20:46,759
I still have to go back to work.

284
00:20:47,500 --> 00:20:48,440
Cen Ye's back

285
00:20:48,759 --> 00:20:49,700
and there's tons of work.

286
00:20:50,880 --> 00:20:51,759
You can head back first.

287
00:20:57,299 --> 00:20:57,759
Fine.

288
00:20:58,980 --> 00:20:59,920
Get some rest.

289
00:21:00,440 --> 00:21:01,259
Call me anytime

290
00:21:01,720 --> 00:21:02,700
if you need me.

291
00:21:20,380 --> 00:21:20,980
Let me send you back.

292
00:21:21,440 --> 00:21:22,200
No, thanks.

293
00:21:22,400 --> 00:21:23,759
I'll take a taxi home myself.

294
00:22:16,960 --> 00:22:17,559
Therefore,

295
00:22:17,799 --> 00:22:19,200
based on our investigation,

296
00:22:19,599 --> 00:22:21,299
we conclude that

297
00:22:21,299 --> 00:22:22,480
the legal representative is

298
00:22:22,599 --> 00:22:23,880
Liu Binbo's third-party partner

299
00:22:24,500 --> 00:22:25,099
and he is suspected of engaging in

300
00:22:25,099 --> 00:22:26,339
commercial violations.

301
00:22:26,920 --> 00:22:27,460
Excuse me.

302
00:22:28,599 --> 00:22:30,380
We are fully aware of Mr. Liu's situation,

303
00:22:30,720 --> 00:22:32,059
but these are all leftover procedural issues.

304
00:22:32,539 --> 00:22:33,299
We will definitely resolve them

305
00:22:33,299 --> 00:22:34,200
within this month.

306
00:22:34,660 --> 00:22:35,539
Could we delay

307
00:22:35,839 --> 00:22:37,200
submitting the report to Hongshen?

308
00:22:38,279 --> 00:22:39,539
I understand Mr. Tao's concerns,

309
00:22:40,119 --> 00:22:42,119
yet per audit procedures,

310
00:22:42,119 --> 00:22:43,779
if this process could be suspended,

311
00:22:43,920 --> 00:22:44,460
we wouldn't even need

312
00:22:44,460 --> 00:22:45,299
to sit here discussing it.

313
00:22:45,380 --> 00:22:46,519
It isn't up to them to decide.

314
00:22:48,380 --> 00:22:49,299
Let's move on.

315
00:22:51,559 --> 00:22:52,200
I'll fill you in

316
00:22:52,420 --> 00:22:53,299
on the specifics later.

317
00:22:57,519 --> 00:22:59,240
Isn't this outside your scope of work?

318
00:23:02,359 --> 00:23:03,140
Keep going.

319
00:23:08,920 --> 00:23:09,279
Alright.

320
00:23:29,079 --> 00:23:30,779
Are things really tough with your family?

321
00:23:34,319 --> 00:23:34,940
Not at all.

322
00:23:35,240 --> 00:23:36,480
Nearly everything's sorted out.

323
00:23:38,619 --> 00:23:39,480
You can take a few days off

324
00:23:39,480 --> 00:23:40,359
to rest up.

325
00:23:42,019 --> 00:23:42,440
Thanks, no need.

326
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:44,420
If there's no other work,

327
00:23:44,539 --> 00:23:45,460
I'll leave first.

328
00:24:20,779 --> 00:24:22,039
You haven't had proper meals.

329
00:24:22,440 --> 00:24:23,359
Cold food irritates your stomach.

330
00:24:23,480 --> 00:24:24,099
Drink something warm.

331
00:24:37,839 --> 00:24:39,019
No overtime this weekend, right?

332
00:24:40,660 --> 00:24:41,200
What's up?

333
00:24:43,279 --> 00:24:44,099
I booked train tickets.

334
00:24:44,599 --> 00:24:45,480
Let's go travel somewhere.

335
00:24:47,119 --> 00:24:47,539
Where to?

336
00:24:51,140 --> 00:24:51,680
Riverwood.

337
00:24:58,799 --> 00:24:59,819
If you don't wanna go...

338
00:24:59,960 --> 00:25:00,440
I wanna go.

339
00:25:37,119 --> 00:25:37,599
Come in.

340
00:25:44,680 --> 00:25:45,160
Mr. Bin.

341
00:25:45,980 --> 00:25:47,059
I'd like to ask for leave.

342
00:25:51,940 --> 00:25:52,759
I've assigned staff

343
00:25:53,039 --> 00:25:54,059
to oversee the transport routes.

344
00:25:54,559 --> 00:25:55,819
Emergency response plans are all ready.

345
00:25:56,920 --> 00:25:58,099
All work is fully arranged.

346
00:25:59,000 --> 00:26:00,440
Just don't lose sight of anything important.

347
00:26:04,299 --> 00:26:04,779
Go have a rest.

348
00:26:19,559 --> 00:26:20,480
[I'll be away for a few days.]

349
00:26:21,079 --> 00:26:21,640
[Keep a close eye]

350
00:26:21,640 --> 00:26:22,720
[on Zhang Bin's people.]

351
00:26:33,700 --> 00:26:34,279
Mr. Zhang.

352
00:26:34,559 --> 00:26:35,819
Protesters are causing trouble at the construction site again.

353
00:26:36,099 --> 00:26:36,880
They brought banners

354
00:26:36,880 --> 00:26:38,160
and tried to stage a demonstration downstairs.

355
00:26:38,279 --> 00:26:39,359
We've already dispersed them.

356
00:26:43,359 --> 00:26:44,500
Act on impulse.

357
00:26:46,039 --> 00:26:47,660
If kindness and loyalty could feed people,

358
00:26:48,480 --> 00:26:49,099
he wouldn't have to

359
00:26:49,099 --> 00:26:50,339
come here making trouble.

360
00:26:52,559 --> 00:26:53,200
Keep this in mind:

361
00:26:54,039 --> 00:26:55,140
never be someone

362
00:26:55,440 --> 00:26:56,440
who's utterly loyal

363
00:26:57,559 --> 00:26:58,880
yet lacks good sense.

364
00:27:07,640 --> 00:27:08,500
Why does Chen Yi

365
00:27:08,960 --> 00:27:10,940
ask for personal leave at such a critical time?

366
00:27:11,480 --> 00:27:12,660
Didn't you run into him just now?

367
00:27:16,259 --> 00:27:17,660
Weren't you supposed to have him

368
00:27:17,660 --> 00:27:18,880
lead the convoy for inspection?

369
00:27:19,140 --> 00:27:20,859
Ditching work right when we need him most.

370
00:27:21,220 --> 00:27:22,119
It's abnormal.

371
00:27:23,779 --> 00:27:25,019
Seize the right opportunity with external support,

372
00:27:26,500 --> 00:27:27,539
and execute the plan to draw the enemy away from their stronghold.

373
00:27:30,259 --> 00:27:31,200
This way.

374
00:27:53,599 --> 00:27:54,359
I've confirmed it with the staff.

375
00:27:54,640 --> 00:27:55,559
This train follows the same route

376
00:27:55,799 --> 00:27:56,220
as your first trip

377
00:27:56,220 --> 00:27:57,799
to Vineton.

378
00:27:58,500 --> 00:27:59,980
But it's an hour faster.

379
00:28:00,420 --> 00:28:01,299
We'll arrive in the afternoon.

380
00:28:05,640 --> 00:28:06,380
Let me carry my bag.

381
00:28:08,359 --> 00:28:09,059
After all,

382
00:28:10,119 --> 00:28:11,460
she was the one who brought me here.

383
00:28:28,279 --> 00:28:29,859
Passengers bound for Riverwood,

384
00:28:29,940 --> 00:28:31,660
please line up for boarding here.

385
00:28:32,339 --> 00:28:33,819
Any passengers for Riverwood?

386
00:28:35,140 --> 00:28:36,319
Anyone?

387
00:28:39,839 --> 00:28:40,640
You can also use the other side.

388
00:28:40,640 --> 00:28:41,359
Both boarding gates are available.

389
00:28:41,359 --> 00:28:42,319
Either one is okay.

390
00:28:49,440 --> 00:28:50,279
Keep your hands to yourself.

391
00:28:50,420 --> 00:28:51,059
Hey, I didn't know

392
00:28:51,059 --> 00:28:51,960
you bring an urn

393
00:28:51,960 --> 00:28:52,680
on the train.

394
00:28:52,680 --> 00:28:53,880
Such bad luck.

395
00:28:57,640 --> 00:28:58,039
Excuse me.

396
00:28:58,039 --> 00:28:58,779
Make way, please.

397
00:28:59,380 --> 00:29:00,119
Sir, let go of him.

398
00:29:00,599 --> 00:29:01,119
What's going on?

399
00:29:01,380 --> 00:29:01,700
What's going on?

400
00:29:01,700 --> 00:29:02,400
He was rummaging through my bag,

401
00:29:02,539 --> 00:29:03,339
and I caught him red-handed.

402
00:29:03,400 --> 00:29:04,019
I didn't!

403
00:29:04,500 --> 00:29:04,680
Alright,

404
00:29:04,680 --> 00:29:05,799
show me your ID and tickets.

405
00:29:06,400 --> 00:29:06,819
ID and the ticket!

406
00:29:07,799 --> 00:29:08,160
Okay.

407
00:29:08,160 --> 00:29:08,819
Let me find them.

408
00:29:11,779 --> 00:29:12,099
Freeze!

409
00:29:12,839 --> 00:29:13,420
Trying to run?

410
00:29:13,619 --> 00:29:14,079
Freeze!

411
00:29:14,279 --> 00:29:14,960
Come with us.

412
00:29:15,000 --> 00:29:15,400
Run into two mourners

413
00:29:15,400 --> 00:29:16,680
in the morning.

414
00:29:17,140 --> 00:29:17,740
Mind your manners!

415
00:29:17,740 --> 00:29:18,420
Ridiculous!

416
00:29:19,119 --> 00:29:19,579
Move!

417
00:29:21,559 --> 00:29:21,900
Move!

418
00:29:22,720 --> 00:29:23,519
How ridiculous!

419
00:29:25,599 --> 00:29:26,240
Jesus!

420
00:29:27,619 --> 00:29:29,180
How dare they bring an urn with them.

421
00:29:29,940 --> 00:29:30,940
What rotten luck!

422
00:29:51,059 --> 00:29:51,819
It's too crowded inside.

423
00:29:51,980 --> 00:29:52,660
Let me hold it.

424
00:29:59,380 --> 00:30:00,000
You got up so early.

425
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:00,640
Get some sleep.

426
00:30:00,920 --> 00:30:01,700
I'll wake you up when we arrive.

427
00:30:32,920 --> 00:30:33,480
You're awake.

428
00:30:35,859 --> 00:30:36,640
Sleep well?

429
00:30:38,039 --> 00:30:39,059
Sure.

430
00:30:41,539 --> 00:30:42,380
Then my shoulder, as a pillow,

431
00:30:42,380 --> 00:30:43,299
will fetch a good price.

432
00:30:45,819 --> 00:30:47,319
It deserves a good price.

433
00:30:54,619 --> 00:30:55,400
Have some.

434
00:30:59,799 --> 00:31:00,480
What's up?

435
00:31:03,740 --> 00:31:04,539
You're so kind.

436
00:31:07,839 --> 00:31:09,019
Just because of a sausage?

437
00:31:13,180 --> 00:31:14,400
It's more than enough.

438
00:31:16,740 --> 00:31:17,220
Fine.

439
00:31:18,000 --> 00:31:19,460
I'll bring you more next time.

440
00:31:31,660 --> 00:31:32,720
Riverwood is vast.

441
00:31:39,480 --> 00:31:40,220
We're arriving.

442
00:32:02,259 --> 00:32:02,960
Does thin ring a bell?

443
00:32:05,119 --> 00:32:06,740
I was too young back then,

444
00:32:07,200 --> 00:32:08,160
so I barely recall anything.

445
00:32:09,420 --> 00:32:10,200
Well, let me scout the way ahead.

446
00:32:12,119 --> 00:32:13,019
Exit over there.

447
00:32:13,759 --> 00:32:14,460
Take it slow.

448
00:32:14,920 --> 00:32:17,500
Taxi! Taxi!

449
00:32:17,619 --> 00:32:18,019
Easy!

450
00:32:18,019 --> 00:32:18,680
Taxi! Taxi!

451
00:32:21,519 --> 00:32:22,400
Hey guys!

452
00:32:22,880 --> 00:32:23,519
Need a ride?

453
00:32:23,640 --> 00:32:24,559
Where do you wanna go?

454
00:32:24,880 --> 00:32:26,319
When was the station renovated?

455
00:32:26,740 --> 00:32:27,740
It's been five years.

456
00:32:28,359 --> 00:32:29,960
I thought you two were tourists.

457
00:32:29,980 --> 00:32:30,859
You're locals?

458
00:32:30,859 --> 00:32:31,579
Visit family?

459
00:32:31,740 --> 00:32:33,299
I stayed here as a kid.

460
00:32:34,500 --> 00:32:35,859
Could you take us to Nanshan Cemetery?

461
00:32:36,200 --> 00:32:37,700
It is quite far out.

462
00:32:37,900 --> 00:32:38,960
But don't worry.

463
00:32:39,119 --> 00:32:40,500
Just tell me

464
00:32:40,500 --> 00:32:41,059
where you wanna go.

465
00:32:41,140 --> 00:32:43,940
Taxi! Taxi!

466
00:32:58,460 --> 00:32:59,019
Do you wanna visit

467
00:32:59,019 --> 00:33:00,220
your relatives here?

468
00:33:01,839 --> 00:33:02,539
No need.

469
00:33:02,940 --> 00:33:04,440
I only have one aunt here.

470
00:33:04,700 --> 00:33:05,680
When I was very young,

471
00:33:06,339 --> 00:33:07,660
she dumped me on others.

472
00:33:08,740 --> 00:33:10,180
But they don't like me.

473
00:33:11,220 --> 00:33:12,579
So for Wei Mingzhen

474
00:33:12,839 --> 00:33:13,720
and me,

475
00:33:14,859 --> 00:33:15,920
they're not real family.

476
00:33:19,059 --> 00:33:19,660
It's better not to visit them.

477
00:33:21,799 --> 00:33:22,480
Why did you offer to come back

478
00:33:22,480 --> 00:33:23,539
to Riverwood with me?

479
00:33:26,000 --> 00:33:27,240
You just got back to work

480
00:33:27,480 --> 00:33:29,119
and you've been swamped nonstop.

481
00:33:29,680 --> 00:33:30,799
It's good to get away and clear your head.

482
00:33:32,559 --> 00:33:33,240
One's bones

483
00:33:33,799 --> 00:33:35,339
should be laid in one's native land.

484
00:33:43,440 --> 00:33:44,160
These past few days,

485
00:33:44,400 --> 00:33:45,400
you haven't slept well, have you?

486
00:33:47,900 --> 00:33:48,960
Bringing Wei Mingzhen home

487
00:33:49,960 --> 00:33:51,480
will lift a huge weight off your heart.

488
00:33:54,160 --> 00:33:54,720
Thank you.

489
00:33:57,059 --> 00:33:57,740
My pleasure.

490
00:34:28,559 --> 00:34:29,340
This is the plot

491
00:34:29,920 --> 00:34:30,460
reserved

492
00:34:30,460 --> 00:34:31,519
by Ms. Miao.

493
00:34:32,260 --> 00:34:33,119
It's quiet and secluded

494
00:34:33,239 --> 00:34:34,159
with an open view.

495
00:34:35,000 --> 00:34:35,780
All cemetery facilities here

496
00:34:35,780 --> 00:34:36,860
are fully equipped.

497
00:34:37,280 --> 00:34:38,320
We provide

498
00:34:38,420 --> 00:34:39,739
full services,

499
00:34:40,099 --> 00:34:41,139
from custom headstone engraving

500
00:34:41,780 --> 00:34:42,559
to regular grave upkeep.

501
00:34:42,760 --> 00:34:43,199
You don't need to

502
00:34:43,260 --> 00:34:44,219
worry about it at all.

503
00:35:07,219 --> 00:35:08,159
We'll close the crypt.

504
00:35:08,360 --> 00:35:09,340
Please step aside.

505
00:35:29,780 --> 00:35:30,460
My condolences.

506
00:35:35,039 --> 00:35:35,940
We'll take our leave now.

507
00:35:50,380 --> 00:35:51,679
Finally, she's back home.

508
00:35:57,500 --> 00:35:58,360
Back home...

509
00:36:18,880 --> 00:36:20,320
When I was a kid,

510
00:36:21,539 --> 00:36:23,380
it always snows in winter.

511
00:36:24,739 --> 00:36:26,519
The snow would pile up to my ankles.

512
00:36:29,599 --> 00:36:30,619
Winters in Vineton

513
00:36:31,099 --> 00:36:32,039
only bring endless rain.

514
00:36:34,579 --> 00:36:35,980
That's why I was confused at first,

515
00:36:35,980 --> 00:36:37,179
wondering

516
00:36:38,340 --> 00:36:40,000
where the winter had gone.

517
00:36:41,659 --> 00:36:43,119
Winter was my favorite season

518
00:36:43,739 --> 00:36:45,119
when I was here.

519
00:36:46,699 --> 00:36:47,579
I could sneak out

520
00:36:48,619 --> 00:36:50,039
to play in the snow.

521
00:36:51,480 --> 00:36:53,079
And winter meant

522
00:36:53,840 --> 00:36:54,739
the Chinese Lunar New Year is arriving.

523
00:36:57,519 --> 00:36:58,880
Every New Year,

524
00:37:00,400 --> 00:37:01,440
all other kids

525
00:37:02,380 --> 00:37:04,260
would get new clothes from their moms.

526
00:37:06,300 --> 00:37:07,280
But I never got one.

527
00:37:10,199 --> 00:37:11,500
I remember I always sat

528
00:37:11,500 --> 00:37:13,179
on the threshold of my aunt's house,

529
00:37:14,360 --> 00:37:15,780
staring off

530
00:37:17,619 --> 00:37:18,780
and waiting for my mom to pick me up.

531
00:37:21,300 --> 00:37:23,219
Yet she never came.

532
00:37:28,500 --> 00:37:29,139
Then

533
00:37:31,239 --> 00:37:32,659
one day,

534
00:37:34,820 --> 00:37:35,920
she told me.

535
00:37:37,420 --> 00:37:37,920
Jing,

536
00:37:39,699 --> 00:37:40,500
let me take you away.

537
00:37:42,699 --> 00:37:43,760
We have our home.

538
00:37:46,260 --> 00:37:47,980
You can't imagine how happy I was.

539
00:37:51,480 --> 00:37:52,420
But soon after,

540
00:37:54,920 --> 00:37:55,900
she left me

541
00:37:55,900 --> 00:37:56,900
somewhere else again.

542
00:38:24,940 --> 00:38:25,619
Chen Yi,

543
00:38:29,320 --> 00:38:30,780
my mom was really gone.

544
00:38:43,739 --> 00:38:44,280
I'm here.

545
00:39:18,239 --> 00:39:19,420
What if we stay here?

546
00:39:20,679 --> 00:39:21,139
Wouldn't that be nice

547
00:39:21,139 --> 00:39:22,260
to stay here?

548
00:39:26,599 --> 00:39:27,000
Okay.

549
00:39:30,239 --> 00:39:31,400
Then tell me

550
00:39:32,260 --> 00:39:33,719
what would I do here?

551
00:39:36,159 --> 00:39:37,559
You don't have to do anything at all.

552
00:39:38,739 --> 00:39:39,639
Support me again?

553
00:39:40,599 --> 00:39:41,239
Nope.

554
00:39:41,360 --> 00:39:42,159
I can't afford you.

555
00:39:48,360 --> 00:39:49,440
In Riverwood,

556
00:39:50,800 --> 00:39:52,079
we could open a little shop

557
00:39:53,480 --> 00:39:54,519
7/24.

558
00:39:56,239 --> 00:39:57,139
You take the day shift

559
00:39:57,760 --> 00:39:58,599
and I'll work nights.

560
00:39:59,619 --> 00:40:00,519
We could put a small bed

561
00:40:01,039 --> 00:40:01,920
in the storage room,

562
00:40:02,980 --> 00:40:03,780
which will save on rent

563
00:40:04,579 --> 00:40:05,420
and stick to regular mealtimes.

564
00:40:10,500 --> 00:40:11,099
Sounds good.

565
00:40:12,760 --> 00:40:13,539
But what about you?

566
00:40:14,659 --> 00:40:16,039
You once said

567
00:40:16,519 --> 00:40:17,440
paying for my schooling

568
00:40:17,440 --> 00:40:18,800
was a long-term investment.

569
00:40:19,960 --> 00:40:20,659
You wanted me to

570
00:40:20,659 --> 00:40:22,199
move to a big city

571
00:40:23,340 --> 00:40:24,519
and land a decent job.

572
00:40:25,260 --> 00:40:26,199
If we just open

573
00:40:26,199 --> 00:40:27,260
a little shop here,

574
00:40:28,579 --> 00:40:29,880
won't your investment go to waste?

575
00:40:32,519 --> 00:40:33,260
Did I...

576
00:40:33,559 --> 00:40:34,880
really say such awful things back then?

577
00:40:36,099 --> 00:40:37,119
Lots of.

578
00:40:41,440 --> 00:40:42,800
I was such a jerk before.

579
00:42:19,699 --> 00:42:20,940
Such a pretty girl

580
00:42:20,940 --> 00:42:21,840
and good-looking guy!

581
00:42:22,260 --> 00:42:23,780
Are you two here for your honeymoon?

582
00:42:24,760 --> 00:42:26,539
The Mid-Autumn Festival is arriving in just a few days.

583
00:42:26,679 --> 00:42:27,179
Sir,

584
00:42:27,440 --> 00:42:28,300
get your pretty wife

585
00:42:28,300 --> 00:42:29,420
a gold necklace.

586
00:42:29,559 --> 00:42:30,280
It'll be such a festive gift!

587
00:42:31,659 --> 00:42:32,320
You like it?

588
00:42:33,900 --> 00:42:35,360
You really think

589
00:42:35,360 --> 00:42:36,880
we can afford gold necklaces for the festival?

590
